    public abstract class AbstractImmutableMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ImmutableMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class for implementing ImmutableMaps. Sub-classes only need to provide implementations for SizedIterable.size() and iterator(). However, sub-classes are advised to also provide implementations for get(Object) and containsKey(Object) as the default implementations run in linear time whereas map's are usually expected to be more efficient than that.
